Why does it exist?

Email RFC rules are complex

Writing a perfect regex is risky

Ruby provides a well-tested, maintained solution

Rails encourages reuse instead of custom regex

What problem does it solve?

It validates:

Presence of @

Valid local and domain parts

No illegal characters

Common real-world email formats

But it does NOT:

Check if email exists

Send verification

Guarantee RFC perfection

